node.text: This week on Worst Firsts I talk to my friends and partners in surgery @DrBenTalei & and @RobertCohenMD and get the scoop and the dos and donts in plastic surgery, fillers, and more. So if you are considering doing anything to augment yourself, I suggest you check this out! They also tell me about their lives before being surgeons and of course their WORSTS. You won't want to miss it! Also make sure to check out Ben's podcast The Reality Pill Podcast- available on all podcast streaming platforms.

node.text:
This week on Worst Firsts I have actor @DarrenBarnet and we talk about his worst first date with one of the shallow ladies of LA (Not all of us but there's a bunch), his jobs prior to acting, how he got "discovered" (lucky SOB) and how to deal with loss. It's a great one. Make sure to check out Darren on the hit show @NeverHaveIEver on @Netflix <3
Who do you want see next on Worst Firsts?

node.text: Ok this episode of Worst Firsts covers A LOT. The move we are going through, a girl on Tik Tok trying to "cancel" me and most importantly- YOUR WORSTS. There were so many submissions I couldn't get to them all but if you love this segment let me know and I'll do listener submissions more often! You guys shared EVERYTHING; ghost stories, getting too high, bad dates and more! You won't want to miss this one! Full episode here and on youtube (Link in bio)

node.text: Ok, as you can tell by my face this episode of WORST FIRSTS with @cherdleys was one of my faves. We dug deep in this one but not too deep bro. We basically realized that most human beings played doctor as kids and it was mad inappropriate but no one talks about that. Also Chad tells me a worst about how he got pressured into dating a girl he didn't even like. GNARLY DUDE. Anyway if you actually stop your ADD brain for two minutes and sit through this episode I PROMISE we will make you laugh

node.text: Musician and YouTuber (and boyfriend of former guest Tara Yummy) Jake Webber joins us to talk about all the messed up stuff he's collected over the years from famous serial killers like John Wayne Gacy and Richard Ramirez. Jake talks about how he got into the "murderabilia" game and also talks about the time he and his friend started a small bonfire that ultimately turned into a massive fire that nearly burned his entire hometown down. It's a hoot. Tune in :)

node.text: Ok, this episode's guest, the wonderful Dee Wallace came about in such a serendipitous way: I was watching a talk by Dolores Cannon on youtube about life after death and was listening to names of people she talked about because I wanted to interview someone who knew her on Worst Firsts. Well, one of the first names she mentioned was Dee Wallace! SO, I go to instagram and look for Dee Wallace, and look on her page, AND I see a photo of her with my previous podcast guest @thegabriellestone! AND THEN I find out Gabrielle is her DAUGHTER. Life is really special and I AM TELLING YOU, these things happen when (I feel) you are following the path that is truest to what you should be doing in your life. Anyway, please tune into this episode with lovely Dee, she has been in classic films like ET and Cujo yet is also such a spiritual/enlightening/incredible human being and this episode was pure joy. Full episode here, we well as on Youtube and everywhere else you find podcasts :)

node.title: WORST FIRSTS WITH SPIRITUAL HEALER AND ACTRESS @TheDeeWallace

node.text: OK so @sethgreen and I go back- Seth has been a dear friend and directed my first pilot for TBS back in 2015. He has been in this business since he was a wee tot and has had an incredible career from Buffy the Vampire Slayer, to co-creating Robot Chicken to Austin Powers, to voicing Chris on Family Guy and the list goes on. In this episode of Worst Firsts we talk about one time when he had an INTENSE audition with a huge director and things went.... well you have to watch to find out. The full episode is available here as well as itunes and youtube! Who do you want to see next on Worst Firsts?

node.text:
Comedian and host of the "Back to School" podcast @MazJobrani sits down with me to talk about his terrible time shooting a Chuck Norris movie where he was forced to play a stereotypical terrorist character and had to do his own stunts. Plus, he tells me all about how his family moved here during the Iranian revolution, the culture shock of living in America, and how his family dealt with racism. FULL EPISODE HERE & ON YOUTUBE 

 www.youtube.com/brittanyfurlan

Check Maz's YouTube channel here: https://www.youtube.com/channel/UCwI6DzqXhYL-DTwPcOZ-WDQ

node.text: I asked the people of Twitter who they wanted to see next on Worst Firsts and it was my little pixie punk cutie pie @Tarayummyy. Tara grew up in LA and was always a cutie pie, but unfortunately her cutie-pie-ness gained her some unwanted attention- a STALKER. Tune into this episode to hear Tara's Worst First and make sure to subscribe to her youtube channel!!! She's the best <3

node.text: Happiest birthday ever to my sister @Mikaela ✨💫We have been through it ALL (literally). I am forever flattered anytime anyone thinks we are twins (except I’d be the one who ate all the food in the womb and prob would’ve eaten you too) You are my little gremlin. A beauty inside & out. I can’t wait to celebrate ur 7th bday with you in a week doing gremlin things 👹 Here’s a flashback of some of our most interesting moments/looks 🧐😂 Love you (and you know the word I wanna call you but I can’t say it on here or ever for that matter) xxx 💋
